  "text": "HTTP filter factory registration and per-connection instantiation in Envoy follows this architecture:\n\n## Filter Factory Registry and Registration\n\nThe filter factory system is defined in envoy/server/filter_config.h. Each HTTP filter must implement the **NamedHttpFilterConfigFactory** interface (line 273), which provides the method **createFilterFactoryFromProto()** (lines 286-288). This method takes a protobuf configuration and returns an **Http::FilterFactoryCb** - a callback function that instantiates filters.\n\nConvenience base classes are provided in source/extensions/filters/http/common/factory_base.h. The **FactoryBase** template class (line 63) inherits from NamedHttpFilterConfigFactory and handles protobuf message validation and downcasting, reducing boilerplate in filter implementations. Filters register themselves using LEGACY_REGISTER_FACTORY macro or equivalent registry mechanisms.\n\n## Per-Connection Filter Chain Initialization\n\nWhen the HTTP connection manager receives a new connection, it creates an HttpConnectionManagerConfig from the protobuf configuration. During initialization (source/extensions/filters/network/http_connection_manager/config.cc, lines 709-714), the **Http::FilterChainHelper::processFilters()** method iterates through the configured HTTP filters. For each filter, it:\n\n1. Retrieves the registered NamedHttpFilterConfigFactory for that filter (line 134, filter_chain_helper.h)\n2. Calls the factory's createFilterFactoryFromProto() method (line 145)\n3. Creates a filter config provider and stores the factory callback (line 155-156)\n\nThese callbacks are stored in filter_factories_ member of HttpConnectionManagerConfig.\n\n## Per-Request Filter Chain Creation\n\nWhen a new HTTP stream arrives on the connection, the connection manager (source/common/http/conn_manager_impl.h) creates an ActiveStream and calls decodeHeaders(). At line 1348 in conn_manager_impl.cc, decodeHeaders() calls **filter_manager_.createFilterChain()**.\n\nThe FilterManager::createFilterChain() (source/common/http/filter_manager.h, line 849) delegates to the **HttpConnectionManagerConfig::createFilterChain()** method (lines 141-143 in config.h), which calls **Http::FilterChainUtility::createFilterChainForFactories()** (source/common/http/filter_chain_helper.cc, line 17).\n\nThis function iterates through the stored filter factories and for each one calls **FilterManager::applyFilterFactoryCb()** (filter_manager.h, line 697), passing a **FilterChainFactoryCallbacksImpl** instance as the manager.\n\n## Per-Request Filter Instantiation\n\nEach filter factory callback is invoked with a FilterChainFactoryCallbacksImpl (source/common/http/filter_manager.h, lines 913-949). The factory implementation calls methods on this callbacks object to add filters:\n\n- **addStreamDecoderFilter()** (line 918) creates an **ActiveStreamDecoderFilter** wrapper (line 920-921) around the actual filter instance\n- **addStreamEncoderFilter()** (line 924) creates an **ActiveStreamEncoderFilter** wrapper (line 926-927)\n- **addStreamFilter()** (line 930) creates both decoder and encoder filter wrappers for dual-purpose filters\n\nThese ActiveStreamDecoderFilter and ActiveStreamEncoderFilter wrappers manage the filter lifecycle, handle filter callbacks, and coordinate iteration through the filter chain during request/response processing.\n\nThe actual filter instances are created at line 920-921 (decoder) and 926-927 (encoder) through the factory callbacks. Each stream gets its own independent set of filter instances, allowing per-stream state management and filtering logic."
